The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Thursday, February 06, 2003 				 Fugitive held
																								Serampore, Feb. 5: Illegal arms dealer Shyambabu Bind, who had escaped from Serampore court last Saturday, was recaptured from Walsh Hospital today. 																								Bind told police he had escaped to foil the wedding of his paramour to another person. 																								He had raided the girls house last night to elope with her. But her parents raised an alarm and local youths cornered Bind and his three armed friends. 																								They escaped, but Bind was beaten unconscious. Seoraphuli police officials rescued him and took him to hospital, where the Serampore police, on a tip-off, arrested him. 
